Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unregister_gui_edit_callback(25.10)        unregister_gui_edit_callback(25.10)

Name
       unregister_gui_edit_callback  -  Removes the callback function from the
       specified move action

Syntax
       unregister_gui_edit_callback

       [-help]

       -command <string>

        -edit_type {selection pre-move post-move}

       Removes the callback function from the specified move action.  In  GUI,
       the move action involves the following three steps:

              * Click an object.

              * Move the object to the new location.

              * Click to place the object at the new location and complete the
                move.

       The callback function is implemented based on the move action specified
       with the -edit_type parameter.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  the  usage of the command. For a detailed description of
              the command, use the man command:

              man unregister_gui_edit_callback

       -command <string>
              Specifies the name of the callback function.

       -edit_type {selection pre-move post-move}
              Specifies the GUI edit function:

              * selection - Implements the callback function when an object is
                selected (after Step 1).

              * pre-move - Implements the callback function  just  before  the
                object  is  placed at the new location (after Step 2, just be-
                fore you change the coordinates in Step 3).

              * post-move - Implements the callback function after  an  object
                is moved (after Step 3, when the tool updates the DB records).

Example
       Consider the following proc definition:

       proc move_event_callback {

            set objList [dbGet selected]

            foreach obj $objList {

                  set type [dbGet $obj.objType]

                  if {$type == "sdp"} {

                       custom_snap_sdp $obj

                  } elseif {$type == "inst"} {

                       set cellName [dbGet $obj.cell.name]

                       if {[regexp grf $cellName]} {

                            custom_snap_grf $obj

                       }

                  }

       }

       }

       The  following command triggers the move_event_callback function on the
       selected object just before the move is completed:

       register_gui_edit_callback      -edit_type      pre_move       -command
       move_event_callback

       The  following  command removes the callback to the move_event_callback
       function:

       unregister_gui_edit_callback     -edit_type      pre_move      -command
       move_event_callback

